    "summary": "Illustrates the frontend structure of a dApp, showing page navigation, user dashboards, and integration with blockchain smart contracts and Firebase.",
    "whatItShows": "This diagram outlines the high-level frontend architecture of a decentralized application (dApp). It starts with the main App.tsx component, routing to core pages like HomePage, LoginPage, and SignupPage. From the HomePage, users can access specific dashboards for Farmer, Distributor, Retailer, or a Customer QR Scanner. All these user-facing components interact with a central Blockchain Service, which in turn communicates with a Smart Contract and Firebase for data storage and decentralized logic.",
    "whenToUse": "To visualize the overall structure of a dApp's frontend and its primary backend integrations. When designing the user flow and component hierarchy for a web application involving blockchain. To explain the interaction points between the frontend, blockchain logic, and traditional backend services like Firebase. For onboarding new developers to a project with a similar architecture.",
